\subsection{Data preparation}

There are three growing seasons in India: Kharif (autumn), Rabi (winter) and summer. MapSPAM data was temporally disaggregated from annual to seasonal data using crop calendars from FAO Aquastat and MIRCA2000 \citep{portmann_2010}. The initial condition for this simulation is taken from maps of crop area in 1960; the first in a time series of crop distribution maps. Estimates of cropland extent between 1960--2005 are retrieved from a spatio-temporal reconstruction of land use/land cover in India \citep{moulds}. \\

